import React from 'react'
import Form from 'react-bootstrap/Form';
import Button from 'react-bootstrap/Button';
import {Container, Row, Col} from "react-bootstrap"
import { Link } from 'react-router-dom';



export const DosageCats = () => {
  return (
    <>
    <Container fluid>
    <Form className = "rounded p-4 p-sm-3">

    <Row className = "rowD">
      <Col>
      <Form.Select aria-label="Default select example">
      <option>How much food you need based on your cats weight ?</option>
      <option value="1">2kg = 140g</option>
      <option value="2">3kg = 190g</option>
      <option value="3">4kg = 230g</option>
      <option value="4">5kg = 280g</option>
    </Form.Select>
    </Col>
    <Col>
    <Form.Select aria-label="Default select example">
      <option>How much water you need based on your cats weight ?</option>
      <option value="1">2kg = 140ml</option>
      <option value="2">3kg = 200ml</option>
      <option value="3">4kg = 260ml</option>
      <option value="4">5kg = 320ml</option>
    </Form.Select>
      </Col>
    </Row>
      
    <Row>
      <Col>
      <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicEmail">
        <Form.Label>Email address</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control type="email" placeholder="Enter email" />
        <Form.Text className="text-muted">
          We'll never share your email with anyone else.
        </Form.Text>
      </Form.Group>

      </Col>
    <Col>
      <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicPassword">
        <Form.Label>Password</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control type="password" placeholder="Password" />
      </Form.Group>
      
      </Col>
      </Row>
    <Row>
    
    <Col>
      <Button variant="primary" type="submit">
        Submit
      </Button>
      </Col>
  <Col>
      <Link to = "/">
      <Button variant="secondary">
        Home
      </Button>
      </Link>
      </Col>
    </Row>
    </Form>
      
      
    </Container>
      
      
      </>
      
  )
}
